<section xml:id="sec-double-angle-identities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Double-Angle Identities</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Identities about double angles can be derived from the sum and difference identities.
    </p>
    
    <md>
      <mrow>
        \begin{array}{ccc}
        \boxed{\sin{(2\theta)} = 2\sin{\theta}\cos{\theta}} \amp \quad \boxed{\begin{array}{rl}
        \cos{(2\theta)} \amp = \cos^2{\theta} - \sin^2{\theta} \\
        \amp = 2\cos^2{\theta} - 1 \\
        \amp = 1 - 2\sin^2{\theta}
        \end{array}}
        \amp \quad \boxed{\tan{(2\theta)} = \frac{2\tan{\theta}}{1 - \tan^2{\theta}}}
        \end{array}
      </mrow>
    </md>
    
    <p>
      These are expressions for the trigonometric ratios of double angles (<m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m>, and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>), in terms of their associated <q>single</q> angles (<m>\sin{\theta}, \cos{\theta}</m>, and <m>\tan{\theta}</m>).
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-finding-exact-value-examples">
    <title>Finding Exact Value Examples</title>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-evaluate-expressions-double-angle">
      <title>Evaluate Exact Expressions</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Evaluate each expression exactly, using a double-angle identity.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2 \sin{\frac{\pi}{12}} \cos{\frac{\pi}{12}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\frac{1}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cos^2{\brac{\frac{\pi}{3}}} - \sin^2{\brac{\frac{\pi}{3}}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\frac{1}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{2 \tan \frac{\pi}{6}}{1 - \tan^2 \frac{\pi}{6}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\sqrt{3}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>1 - 2 \sin^2 15^\circ</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2 \sin \frac{\pi}{6} \cos \frac{\pi}{6}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-expand-expressions-double-angle">
      <title>Expand Expressions</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Expand each expression, using a double-angle identity.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>3\sin{4x}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p><m>4x = 2 \cdot 2x</m> (<m>4x</m> is double <m>2x</m>).</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>6\sin{2x}\cos{2x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\tan{6x}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p><m>6x = 2 \cdot 3x</m> (<m>6x</m> is double <m>3x</m>).</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>\frac{8\tan{3x}}{1 - \tan^2{3x}}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{1}{2}\sin{\frac{1}{2}x}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p><m>\frac{1}{2}x = 2 \cdot \frac{1}{4}x</m>.</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>\sin{\frac{x}{4}}\cos{\frac{x}{4}}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{1}{4}\tan{\frac{1}{2}x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\frac{1}{2}\cdot\frac{\tan{\frac{x}{4}}}{1 - \tan^2{\frac{x}{4}}}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-exact-values-variable-angles">
    <title>Exact Values with Variable Angles</title>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-find-exact-value-variable-angles">
      <title>Find Exact Values</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Find the exact value of each trigonometric ratio, from the given information.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>If <m>\sin{\theta} = \frac{5}{13}</m> and <m>\frac{\pi}{2} \lt \theta \lt \pi</m>. Find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{169}, \cos{(2\theta)} = \frac{119}{169}, \tan{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{119}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>If <m>\cos{\theta}=\frac{2}{5}</m> and <m>\theta</m> is in quadrant IV, find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)}=-\frac{4\sqrt{21}}{25}, \cos{(2\theta)}=-\frac{17}{25}, \tan{(2\theta)}=\frac{4\sqrt{21}}{17}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>If <m>\sin{\theta} = \frac{12}{13}</m>, where <m>\frac{\pi}{2} \lt \theta \lt \pi</m>, then find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{169}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{119}{169}, \tan{(2\theta)} = \frac{120}{119}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>Let <m>\cos{\theta} = -\frac{7}{25}</m> and <m>\ang{90} \lt \theta \lt \ang{180}</m>. Find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = -\frac{336}{625}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{527}{625}, \tan{(2\theta)} = \frac{336}{527}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>Let <m>\theta</m> be an angle in quadrant III with <m>\cos{\theta} = -\frac{8}{17}</m>. Find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = \frac{240}{289}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{161}{289}, \tan{(2\theta)} = -\frac{240}{161}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>If <m>\sin{\theta} = -\frac{12}{13}</m> and <m>\theta</m> is in quadrant III, find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}, \cos{(2\theta)}</m> and <m>\tan{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)} = \frac{120}{169}, \cos{(2\theta)} = -\frac{119}{169}, \tan{(2\theta)} = -\frac{120}{119}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>If <m>\cos{\theta} = -\frac{3}{5}</m> and <m>\theta</m> is in quadrant III, find <m>\sin{(2\theta)}</m>.</p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p><m>\sin{(2\theta)}=\frac{24}{25}</m>.</p>
        </answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-simplify-double-angle-identities">
    <title>Simplify Using Double-Angle Identities</title>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-simplify-expressions-1">
      <title>Simplify Expressions I</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each expression into a single trigonometric function.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2 \sin{(4x)} \cos{(4x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\sin{(8x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>10 \cos^2{x} - 5</m></statement>
        <answer><m>5 \cos{(2x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2 \sin{\brac{\frac{1}{2} x}} \cos{\brac{\frac{1}{2} x}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\sin{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>1 - 2 \sin^2{(3x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\cos{(6x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{2 \sin{x}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\cos{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>6 \sin{(8x)} \cos{(8x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>3 \sin{(16x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>6\sin^2{x}-3</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-3\cos{(2x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\cos^2{(5x)}-4\sin^2{(5x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>4\cos{(10x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\cos^2{(2x)}-2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>2\cos{(4x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\sin{(3x)}\cos{(3x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>2\sin{(6x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2\cos^2{(8x)}-1</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\cos{(16x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>8\sin{(5x)}\cos{(5x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>4\sin{(10x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\sin{\brac{\frac{x}{2}}}\cos{\brac{\frac{x}{2}}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>2\sin{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2\sin^2{(2x)}-2\cos^2{(2x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-2\cos{(4x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-simplify-expressions-2">
      <title>Simplify Expressions II</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each expression into a single trigonometric function.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{4\tan{(3x)}}{1 - \tan^2{(3x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>2 \tan{(6x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\cos{(2x)} - 1}{2 \sin{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>choose the double angle for cosine which cancels out the <m>-1</m> in the numerator.</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>-\sin{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4 \sin^2{(2x)} - 2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-2 \cos{(4x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{6\tan{(4x)}}{1-\tan^2{(4x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>3\tan{(8x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\cos{(2x)} + 1}{2 \cos{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>choose the double angle for cosine which cancels out the <m>1</m> in the numerator.</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>\cos{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{8\tan{(4x)}}{1-\tan^2{(4x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>4\tan{(8x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2\sin{(6x)}\brac{\cos^2{(3x)}-\sin^2{(3x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\sin{(12x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{1}{4}\sec{(6x)}\csc{(6x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\frac{1}{2\sin{(12x)}}</m> or <m>\frac{1}{2}\csc{(12x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\sin^2{\brac{\frac{x}{2}}}-2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-2\cos{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{(6x)}}{2\sin{(3x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\cos{(3x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-simplify-expressions-3">
      <title>Simplify Expressions III</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each expression into a single trigonometric function.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{\cos{(2x)} + 1}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>choose the double angle for cosine which cancels out the 1 in the denominator.</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>\tan{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\cos^3{x}}{\cos{(2x)} + \sin^2{x}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\cos{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin^3{x}}{\cos{(2x)}-\cos^2{x}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\sin{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{3-6\sin^2{x}}{2\sin{x}\cos{x}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>3 \cot{(2x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\brac{\sin^2{x} - \cos^2{x}}^2 - \sin^2{(2x)}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>use a double-angle identity, do not expand.</p>
        </hint>
        <answer><m>\cos{(4x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{2\tan{(2x)}}{3-3\tan^2{(2x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\frac{1}{3}\tan{(4x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sec{(8x)}\brac{\sin^2{(4x)}-\cos^2{(4x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-1</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{1}{2}\cot{(4x)}\brac{1-\tan^2{(4x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\cot{(8x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(4x)}\csc{(2x)}-2\cos{(2x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(4x)}-\brac{\sin{(2x)}+\cos{(2x)}}^2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-1</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin^4{(3x)}-\cos^4{(3x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\cos{(6x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{2}{1-\cos{(8x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\csc^2{(4x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{4}{\tan{(3x)}-\cot{(3x)}}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-2\tan{(6x)}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-equations-double-angle-identities">
    <title>Equations with Double-Angle Identities</title>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-solve-equations-1">
      <title>Solve Equations I</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Solve each equation, by finding all solutions in the interval <m>[0,2\pi)</m>.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(2x)}=\cos{x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{6},\frac{5\pi}{6},\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{3\pi}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(2x)}-2\cos^2{x}=0</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{4},\frac{5\pi}{4},\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{3\pi}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(2x)}=\sqrt{2}\cos{x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{4},\frac{3\pi}{4},\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{3\pi}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>-2\cos{(2x)}=2\sin{x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{7\pi}{6},\frac{11\pi}{6}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(2x)}+\cos{x}=0</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{7\pi}{6},\frac{3\pi}{2},\frac{11\pi}{6}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>2\sin{x}\cos{x}=\cos{(2x)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{8},\frac{5\pi}{8},\frac{9\pi}{8},\frac{13\pi}{8}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{x}+\cos{(2x)}=1</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=0,\frac{\pi}{6},\frac{5\pi}{6},\pi</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{1}{2}\sin{(2x)}-\cos^2{x}=0</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{4},\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{5\pi}{4},\frac{3\pi}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>3\sin{x}+\cos{(2x)}=2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{6},\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{5\pi}{6}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cos{(2x)}=\sin{x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{6},\frac{5\pi}{6},\frac{3\pi}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cos{(2x)}-3\sin{x}=2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{7\pi}{6},\frac{11\pi}{6},\frac{3\pi}{2}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cos{(2x)}-5\cos{x}=2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{2\pi}{3},\frac{4\pi}{3}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>3\cos{(2x)}+2\sin^2{x}=2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{6},\frac{5\pi}{6},\frac{7\pi}{6},\frac{11\pi}{6}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\tan{(2x)}+\tan{x}=0</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=0,\frac{\pi}{3},\frac{2\pi}{3},\pi,\frac{4\pi}{3},\frac{5\pi}{3}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-solve-equations-2">
      <title>Solve Equations II</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Solve each equation, by finding all solutions in the interval <m>[0,2\pi)</m>.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cos{(4x)}+2\cos^2{(2x)}=2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{12},\frac{5\pi}{12},\frac{7\pi}{12},\frac{11\pi}{12},\frac{13\pi}{12},\frac{17\pi}{12},\frac{19\pi}{12},\frac{23\pi}{12}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>5\cos{(2x)}-\cos{x}+3=0</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{3},\frac{5\pi}{3},1.98,4.30</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(2x)}=\cot{x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{\pi}{4},\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{3\pi}{4},\frac{5\pi}{4},\frac{3\pi}{2},\frac{7\pi}{4}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\tan{x}-\cot{x}=2</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x=\frac{3\pi}{8},\frac{7\pi}{8},\frac{11\pi}{8},\frac{15\pi}{8}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>4\cos{(2x)}+10\sin{x}-7=0</m></statement>
