      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-proving-identities-double-angles">
    <title>Proving Identities with Double Angles</title>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-prove-identities-1">
      <title>Prove Identities I</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Prove each trigonometric identity.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\brac{\sin{x} + \cos{x}}^2}{\sin{(2x)}} = \csc{(2x)} + 1</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>Pythagorean identity, double-angle identity.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\csc{x}}{2\cos{x}} = \csc{(2x)}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>reciprocal identity, double-angle identity.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sec^2{x}=\frac{2}{1+\cos{(2x)}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>double-angle identity <m>\cos{(2x)}=2\cos^2{x}-1</m>, rewrite in terms of sine and cosine.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cot{x}\csc{(2x)}=\frac{1}{2\sin^2{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>rewrite in terms of sine and cosine, double-angle identity, cancel common factors.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{1+\cos{(2x)}}{\sin{(2x)}}=\cot x</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>double-angle identity, cancel common factors.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>1+\sin{(2x)}=(\sin{x}+\cos{x})^2</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>expand, Pythagorean identity, double-angle identity.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\tan{x}=\frac{1-\cos{(2x)}}{\sin{(2x)}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>double-angle identity, rewrite in terms of sine and cosine.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\sin{(2x)}\brac{\tan{x}+\cot{x}}=2</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>double-angle identity, rewrite in terms of sine and cosine, distribute, cancel common factors.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{1-\cos{(2x)}} = \cot{x}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>double-angle identity, cancel common factors.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="proj-prove-identities-2">
      <title>Prove Identities II</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Prove each trigonometric identity.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{x}+\tan{x}}{1+\cos{x}}=\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{2 \cos^2{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>start with both sides, double-angle identity, clear denominators, cancel.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{2\tan{x}}{1+\tan^2{x}} = \sin{(2x)}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>convert to sine and cosine, clear denominators, Pythagorean identity, double-angle identity.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{(6x)}}{1 + \cos{(6x)}} = \tan{(3x)}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>work with both sides, double-angle identity, cancel common factors.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\tan{(2x)} = \frac{2}{\cot{x} - \tan{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>work with both sides, rewrite in terms of tangent, simplify complex fraction by clearing denominators.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\cot{x}-\csc{x}=\frac{\cos{(2x)}-\cos{x}}{\sin{(2x)}+\sin{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>work with both sides, double-angle identity, factor quadratic trinomial, cancel common factors, rewrite in terms of sine and cosine, combine fractions (or split fraction).</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{2\cos{x} + 2\cos^2{x}}{\sin{(2x)}} = \frac{\sin{x}}{1 - \cos{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>start with the LHS, double-angle identity, factor out common factor, cancel common factors, multiply by the conjugate.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{1 + \cos{(2x)}} = \frac{\sec^2{x} - 1}{\tan{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>work with both sides, double-angle identity, cancel common factors, Pythagorean identity (or rewrite in terms of sine and cosine, simplify complex fraction by clearing denominators).</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>(\csc{x}-\sin{x})\tan{x}=\frac{\sin{(2x)}}{2\sin{x}}</m></statement>
        <hint>
          <p>work with both sides, double-angle identity, rewrite in terms of sine and cosine, distribute, Pythagorean identity.</p>
        </hint>
      </task>
